The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, April 8: The government today said labour reforms would have to be expedited and changes accepted in the short-term for long-term economic sustainability. Labour reforms should not be seen as just facilitating the closure of a sick industrial unit or laying off employees, Chandrasekhar Sahu, minister of state for labour, said at a seminar organised by the Institute of Company Secretaries of India. 

 New Delhi, April 8: Bajaj Auto today launched an entry-level bike, Platina. The 100-cc bike comes in two versions, priced between Rs 34,000 and Rs 36,000. ?We are confident that the Platina should be able to do about 70,000-75,000 units per month and gradually become the largest selling bike in our portfolio, ahead of CT100,? Bajaj Auto MD Rajiv Bajaj said.

 Hyderabad, April 8: Corporation Bank plans an expansion drive to take its business to Rs 1,00,000 crore and open 60 more branches, CMD B. Sambamurthy said today. The new branches would mostly be in the south.




